The paper deals with linear codes over finite fields, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It also discusses the properties of maximum rank distance (MRD) and non-Gabidulin codes, which are relevant to cryptography (cs.CR). The paper uses algebraic techniques to analyze the genericity of these codes, which could fall under the category of algebraic geometry or algebraic algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the probability of randomly generating MRD and non-Gabidulin codes, which could be considered a statistical analysis (cs.SI). Finally, the paper could be relevant to machine learning and data analysis, as linear codes are used in error correction and data compression (cs.LG).
